21/12/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan voiced support Friday (19 December) for the resumption of negotiations on UN Secretary General Kofi Annan's plan to reunite Cyprus. 
Erdogan said the total rejection of the plan by Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash is wrong, but added that certain aspects of the plan should be revised. 
The international talks on Cyprus issue ended with in March, due to Denktash's unwillingness to compromise. 
On a related note Saturday, Turkish Deputy Prime Minister Mehmet Ali Sahin said Denktash should facilitate rather than complicate Turkish efforts to join the EU. 
(AFP - 20/12/03; AFP, Anadolu Agency - 19/12/03)
